cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with improving the performance of routing in Delay Tolerant Networks (DTN), which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of multipath multicasting to improve scalability and delivery, which involves distributed computing. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a contact information compression algorithm to improve routing performance, which involves information theory. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper addresses the problem of power awareness routing to increase the lifetime of the network, which involves security and cryptography. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with improving the performance of routing in DTN, which involves social and information networks.
